# Organized source layout (monorepo)

When **adding or moving** TypeScript/React files in `packages/` or `apps/`:

## Prefer folders by responsibility

Do not default to piling new files into a single flat directory as the package grows. Use clear buckets (create only what you need):

| Concern                       | Typical folder                                  | Notes                                         |
| ----------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| Shared types only             | `types/` (often `types/index.ts`)               | No React imports in type-only modules.        |
| Pure logic (no hooks, no JSX) | `lib/` or `utils/`                              | Match existing package naming.                |
| React hooks                   | `hooks/`                                        | `use-*.ts`; co-locate `use-*.test.ts`.        |
| UI                            | `components/`                                   | Co-locate `*.test.tsx` next to the component. |
| Server-only / actions         | `server/`, `actions/`, or framework conventions | Follow patterns already in that app.          |

**Workspace packages** with a single entry point often keep a thin **`src/index.ts`** (or package export map) that re-exports the public API only—no heavy logic in the barrel.

**Next.js apps**: follow existing layout (`app/`, `components/`, `lib/` at app root); do not introduce a second competing structure.

## Imports

- **Extensionless** relative imports between local files in source-exported packages (see `typescript-javascript-standards`).
- **Kebab-case** file names (see `typescript-javascript-standards`).

## Tests

- Co-locate **`*.test.ts`** / **`*.test.tsx`** next to the module under test unless the repo already uses a dedicated `__tests__` pattern in that area—then stay consistent with neighbors.

For a fuller checklist and examples, use the **organized-src-structure** skill (`.cursor/skills/organized-src-structure/SKILL.md`).
